Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Dice @sweet potatoes{2%unit} into ½-inch pieces. Core, deseed, and dice @poblano pepper{1%unit} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1%unit} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince one wedge until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4 servings).

Toss sweet potatoes, poblano, and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{5%tsp}, half the @cumin{1%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, divide veggies between 2 baking sheets; roast on top and middle racks.) Roast on top rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, finely dice @roma tomato{1%unit}. Zest and quarter @lime{1%unit} (quarter both limes for 4 servings). Mince @cilantro{1/4%oz} leaves and stems. Mince or grate @garlic{2%clove} (2 cloves for 4). Thinly slice @jalapeño{1%unit} into rounds, removing ribs and seeds for less heat; mince a few slices until you have ½ tsp (1 tsp for 4).

== Creamy Salsa Verde ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp}, cilantro, minced onion, juice from half the lime, a pinch of minced garlic, a pinch of minced jalapeño, a small pinch of cumin (you'll use the rest later), and 1 TBSP olive oil (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Taste and add more garlic if desired. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

== Barramundi ==

Pat @Australis barramundi{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with salt and pepper. Season flesh sides with remaining cumin; rub to evenly coat. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium-high heat. Add barramundi skin sides down. Cook until skin is slightly crisp, ~{4-5%minutes}. Flip and cook until barramundi is opaque and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

== To Serve ==

Toss roasted veggies with tomato and lime zest; divide between #bowls{} or #plates{}. Place barramundi on top. Drizzle with creamy salsa verde and scatter with sliced jalapeño if desired. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.